(Gupta 1990)}{\fs24\lang2057 </X>.
\par <#/>The determina
nts of infant mortality are divided into two main groups, socio-economic and proximate factors. <#/>Socio-economic factors includes education, income, residence, occupation, marital status, health, religion which work through the proximate determinants th
at is maternal factors, environmental contamination, nutrient deficiency and injury.
