\par }{\v <#/>}{\i\v\fs24\lang2057 In the light of structural adjustment which has been taking place in the Tanzania economy, this paper argues for changes in the way education is being financed. }{\v <#/>}{\i\v\fs24\lang2057 
More community involvement and cost sharing is essential so as to avoid fiscal crisis. }{\v <#/>}{\i\v\fs24\lang2057 The new financing formulae will have to grapple with individual needs, local fiscal capacity, lo
cal autonomy, efficient delivery methods, equity, accountability, and financial management capacity. }{\v <#/>}{\i\v\fs24\lang2057 Government transfers will still be required so as to advance the interests of disadvantaged groups and localities.}{
